    <div rend="parallel">
      <p xml:id="PN373-intro">tiṇai, atu. tuṟai, maṟakkaḷavaḻi; ērkkaḷa 
      <app>
      <lem wit="#C8">uruvakamumām</lem>
      <rdg wit="#C2 #C3">aruvakamumām</rdg>
      </app>
      cōḻaṉ kurāppaḷḷit tuñciya kiḷivaḷavaṉ karuvūreṟiṉantāṉaik kōvūrkiḻār.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PN373">
<l>urumicai muḻakkeṉa muraca micaippac</l>
<l>cerunavil vēḻaṅ koṇmū vākat</l>
<l>tērmā vaḻituḷi talaii nāmuṟak</l>
<l>kaṇaikkāṟ ṟeṭutta kaṇṇakaṉ pācaṟai</l>
<l>yiḻitaru kurutiyō ṭēntiya voḷvāṭ</l>
<l>piḻivatu pōlap piṭ<supplied>ṭai</supplied>yū <supplied>ṟu</supplied>vappa</l>
<l>mainta rāṭiya mayaṅkuperun tāṉaik</l>
<l>koṅkupuṟam peṟṟa koṟṟa vēntē</l>
<l><gap quantity="22" reason="lost" unit="character"/>taṇṭa māppoṟi</l>
<l>maṭakkaṇ mayiliyaṉ maṟali yāṅku</l>
<l>neṭuñcuvar nallil pulampak kaṭaikaḻintu</l>
<l>meṉṟōṇ makaḷir maṉṟam pēṇār</l>
<l>puṇṇuva<gap quantity="44" reason="lost" unit="character"/></l>
<l><gap quantity="10" reason="lost" unit="character"/>yaṇiyap puravi vāḻkeṉac</l>
<l>coṉṉiḻa liṉmaiyi ṉaṉṉiḻaṟ cēra</l>
<l>nuṇpūṇ mārpiṟ puṉṟalaic ciṟāa</l>
<l>rampaḻi poḻutiṟ ṟamarmukaṅ kāṇā</l>
<l><gap quantity="19" reason="lost" unit="character"/>ṟ ṟokkāṉa</l>
<l>vēntupuṟaṅ koṭutta vīyntuku paṟantalai</l>
<l>māṭa mayaṅkeri maṇṭik kōṭiṟu</l>
<l>purumeṟi malaiyi ṉirunilañ cērac</l>
<l>ceṉṟōṉ maṉṟa co<g rend="vowel-sign">e</g><gap quantity="12" reason="lost" unit="character"/></l>
<l><gap quantity="11" reason="lost" unit="character"/>ṇṇaṟiṉar kaṇṭukaṇ ṇalaippa</l>
<l>vañci muṟṟam vayakkaḷa ṉāka</l>
<l>vañcā maṟava rāṭpōr paḻittuk</l>
<l>koṇṭaṉai peruma kuṭapulat tatari</l>
<l>polika vattainiṉ paṇaitaṉaṟa<gap quantity="4" reason="lost" unit="character"/>ḷam</l>
<l>viḷaṅkutiṇai vēntar kaḷantoṟuñ ceṉṟu</l>
<l>pukarmuka mukavai polikeṉ ṟēttik</l>
<l>koṇṭaṉa reṉpa periyōr yāṉu</l>
<l>maṅkaṇ mākkiṇai yatira voṟṟa</l>
<l><gap quantity="18" reason="lost" unit="character"/>le ṉāyiṉuṅ kātali ṉētti</l>
<l>niṉṉō raṉṉōr piṟariva ṇiṉmaiyiṉ</l>
<l>maṉṉeyiṉ mukavaikku vanticiṟ peruma</l>
<l>pakaivar pukaḻnta vāṇmai nakaivarkkut</l>
<l>tāviṉ ṟutavum paṇpiṟ pēyoṭu</l>
<l>kaṇanari tiritaru māṅka ṇiṇaṉaruntu</l>
<l>ceñcevi yeruvai kuḻīi</l>
<l>yañcuvaru kiṭakkaiya kaḷaṅkiḻa vōyē.</l>
</lg>
<lg xml:lang="en">
<l corresp="4cd">With a war camp wide in area, where, </l>
<l corresp="1">while drums sound like thunder-sounding thunder, </l>
<l>with fight-trained elephant bulls as clouds,</l>
<l corresp="3">showering dwindling drops of chariot horses, fearfully, </l>
<l corresp="4ab">	the wind raises arrows, </l>
<l corresp="7">with a mixed(?) big army in which warriors dance, </l>
<l corresp="5">while [their] bright swords that they hold up with blood flowing down </l>
<l corresp="6">rejoice in obstacles ???, like squeezing [them] out, </l>
<l corresp="8">o victorious king who obtained the outside of the Koṅku land, </l>
<l><gap quantity="15" reason="lost" unit="character"/></l>
<l corresp="9d-10">thus fighting [their] natures of peacocks with large dots [and] innocent eyes </l>
<l corresp="11">passing the gate so that the good hall with tall walls is lonely, </l>
<l corresp="12">women with soft shoulders won’t mind the village common, </l>
<l>……… </l>
<l corresp="15">in order to join the good shade, in the absence of the shade of words </l>
<l corresp="14">saying “may [your] decorated horses live”, </l>
<l corresp="16">ruddy-headed youngsters, fine ornaments on [their] chests, </l>
<l corresp="17">not seeing the faces of their people at the time arrows destroy [them], </l>
<l>…….</l>
<l corresp="19">in the wasteland, destroyed [and] wasted, on which the king had turned [his] back, </l>
<l corresp="20">thrusting confused flames at the mansions, tusks breaking, </l>
<l corresp="22ab">he who has gone indeed </l>
<l corresp="21">to join the dark ground like a mountain struck by thunder </l>
<l>…………</l>
<l corresp="23">While the eyes are harrassed, seeing, of those who know…, </l>
<l corresp="24">with Vañci as a strong vessel with a courtyard, </l>
<l corresp="25">destroying heaps of men, fearless warriors, </l>
<l corresp="26">you have taken, great man, the thrashing cattle of the western region. </l>
<l corresp="27a-c">May your Paṇai drum flourish. … </l>
<l corresp="28">Going to each battle field of kings with shining families, </l>
<l corresp="29">may those with spotted faces that were drawn by you flourish. – thus praising </l>
<l>they have taken, they say, great people. While I too, (30=</l>
<l corresp="31a-c">beat [my] pretty-eyed Kiṇai drum so that it reverberates, </l>
<l corresp="32">although ………………. praising with love </l>
<l corresp="33">in the absence here of any others who would be like your people, </l>
<l corresp="34">I have come to [your] royal fortress for the things you drew, great man, </l>
<l corresp="39">– you who are the lord of the battle field of expanses to which fear comes, </l>
<l corresp="38">as red-eared kites flock [there] </l>
<l corresp="37">eating fat in that place where jackals roam in hordes </l>
<l corresp="36">along with Pēy of quality who will help without fault, </l>
<l corresp="35">for those who smile at [your] manliness that is praised [even] by [your] enemies. </l>
</lg>
